OL,3,C'Climate Whiplash' puts world's
OL,4,Cbiggest cities at risk of drought and
OL,5,Cflooding
OL,7,FMany of the world's most populous
OL,8,Fcities are increasingly seeing their
OL,9,Fweather flip flop from extreme drought
OL,10,Fto heavy rainfall - a phenomenon that
OL,11,Fhas been dubbed 'climate whiplash' by
OL,12,Fthe charity WaterAid.
OL,14,FFor the first time, a new report by
OL,15,Fthe charity gives us a worldwide, city
OL,16,Fby city breakdown of how our changing
OL,17,Fclimate is affecting water.
OL,19,FToo much water and you get flooding,
OL,20,Ftoo little and you have drought.
