OL,3,C'Climate Whiplash' puts world's
OL,4,Cbiggest cities at risk of drought and
OL,5,Cflooding
OL,7,F"(It) highlights the devastating
OL,8,Fshifts in extreme climate patterns
OL,9,Facross all continents, with the impact
OL,10,Ffelt most clearly on low-income
OL,11,Fcountries, where the absence of water
OL,12,Fbecomes not just a challenge, but a
OL,13,Fmatter of life and death."
OL,15,FColombo in Sri Lanka is seeing the
OL,16,Fmost dramatic shift to more rainfall.
OL,18,FWhilst Cairo in Egypt is drying
OL,19,Ffastest.
