OL,3,C'Climate Whiplash' puts world's
OL,4,Cbiggest cities at risk of drought and
OL,5,Cflooding
OL,7,F17% of cities, including Jakarta in
OL,8,FIndonesia, are experiencing what's
OL,9,Fcalled a 'climate whiplash,' where
OL,10,Fthey swing from extreme wet to extreme
OL,11,Fdry.
OL,13,FProfessor Katerina Michaelides, from
OL,14,Fthe University of Bristol, says this
OL,15,Fphenomenon can be particularly
OL,16,Fdifficult to cope with.
