OL,3,C'Climate Whiplash' puts world's
OL,4,Cbiggest cities at risk of drought and
OL,5,Cflooding
OL,7,F"Places that were historically wet are
OL,8,Fbecoming dry and vice versa," she
OL,9,Fexplained. "Other places are now
OL,10,Fincreasingly battered by both extreme
OL,11,Ffloods and droughts. A deeper
OL,12,Funderstanding of localized climate
OL,13,Fhazards can support more intelligent
OL,14,Fand bespoke planning in major cities."
OL,16,FThe other measure is vulnerability -
OL,17,Fhow geared up cities are to cope?
OL,18,FMadrid, Barcelona and Paris all score
OL,19,Fworse than cities in Australia and
OL,20,FAmerica, because of their aging
OL,21,Finfrastructure.
